'''Alisdair Lamont''' is a [[Scotland|Scottish]] Sports broadcaster who commentates and reports for [[BBC Scotland]]'s ''[[Sportscene]]'' programme<ref>{{cite news|url=http://sport.scotsman.com/rugby/BBC-Scotland-strives-to-make.6217443.jp|title=BBC Scotland strives to make amends on Argentina Test deal ...|date=10 April 2010|publisher=[[BBC Scotland]]|accessdate=12 July 2010}}</ref> and also commentates and occasionally reads the Sports news on [[BBC Radio Scotland]]. Amongst others, he is a respected and insightful commentator who has knowledge of and understands the game, whilst peers might tend to rely on superlatives. Away from work he is a talented musician and family man, father of Patrick (Paddy).

