{{Infobox cricket ground | ground_name = Honor Oak Cricket Club Ground | nickname = | country = England | image = | location = [[Dulwich]], [[London]] | establishment = 1943 (first recorded match) | seating_capacity = | end1 = | end2 = | year1 = | club1 = | date = 29 August | year = 2010 | source = https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/11/595.html Ground profile }}
'''Honor Oak Cricket Club Ground''' is a [[cricket]] ground in [[Dulwich]], [[London]] (formerly [[Surrey]]). The first recorded match on the ground was in 1943, when the Buccaneers played [[Northamptonshire County Cricket Club|Northamptonshire]] in a [[Second World War|wartime]] charity match.<ref>[https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/11/457_misc.html Other matches played on Honor Oak Cricket Club Ground]</ref> In 1967, the ground hosted a single [[Second XI Championship]] match between the [[Surrey County Cricket Club|Surrey Second XI]] and the [[Glamorgan County Cricket Club|Glamorgan Second XI]].<ref>[https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/11/457_sec.html Second XI Championship Matches played on Honor Oak Cricket Club Ground]</ref>
The ground hosted a single [[Women's One Day International cricket|Women's One Day International]] in the [[1993 Women's Cricket World Cup]] when [[Australia women's cricket team|Australia women]] played [[Denmark women's cricket team|Denmark women]].<ref>[https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/11/457_wo.html Women's One-Day International Matches played on Honor Oak Cricket Club Ground]</ref>
In local domestic cricket, the ground is the home venue of [[Alleyn and Honor Oak Cricket Club]].<ref>[http://alleyn.play-cricket.com/home/home.asp? Alleyn and Honor Oak Cricket Club]</ref>
