'''Pakistan Air Force Football Club''', commonly known as '''PAF FC''' is a professional football club based in [[Islamabad]], [[Pakistan]]. It represents the [[Pakistan Air Force]]. The club is currently holders of [[Pakistan National Football Challenge Cup|National Challenge Cup]], after defeating [[WAPDA F.C.|WAPDA]] 2–1 in the finals of [[2018 National Challenge Cup]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://dailytimes.com.pk/238892/paf-clinch-national-challenge-cup-title/ |title=PAF clinch National Challenge Cup title |publisher=Daily Times |date=May 12, 2018 |website=Daily Times |access-date=August 28, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.dawn.com/news/1406898 |title=PAF clinch Challenge Cup title |publisher=DAWN |date=May 11, 2018 |website=DAWN |access-date=August 28, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.footballpakistan.com/2014/04/paf-boss-shahzad-anwar-we-wanted-to-win-the-national-challenge-cup-from-the-start/ |title=PAF BOSS SHAHZAD ANWAR: WE WANTED TO WIN THE NATIONAL CHALLENGE CUP FROM THE START |last=Sohail |first=Shahrukh |publisher=Football Pakistan |date=April 13, 2018 |website=Football Pakistan |access-date=August 28, 2018}}</ref> They got promotion to [[Pakistan Premier League]] from Pakistan Football Federation League after finishing second to [[Baloch F.C.]] in 2007–08 season.
