{{Infobox award|name=Super Eight Most Valuable Player|current_awards=|image=|imagesize=|alt=|caption=|description=Best player in the [[MIAA Division IA Baseball Championship|Super Eight]]|presenter=|country=United States|location=|reward=|year=2014|year2=|holder=[[Scott Creedon]], [[Braintree Wamps|Braintree]]|website=}}
The '''Super Eight Most Valuable Player''' is an award for the best individual performance during the [[MIAA Division IA Baseball Championship|Super Eight]] in [[Brockton, Massachusetts]]. The recipient of the award is announced at the completion of the Super Eight Championship Game. The award is similar to [[Major League Baseball]]'s [[World Series MVP|World Series Most Valuable Player]] award.
Since 2014, the winner of the award has received a wooden bat engraved with the award title.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://espn.go.com/blog/boston/high-school/post/_/id/43138/braintrees-scott-creedon-is-2016-espnboston-mr-baseball|title=Braintree's Scott Creedon is 2016 ESPNBoston Mr. Baseball|access-date=2016-07-08}}</ref> Nobody has yet to win the award from the losing team of the Super Eight Baseball Tournament. The Super Eight started in 2014, and the award has been given out every year, from the start.
Braintree's [[Scott Creedon]] became the first and only player to win back-to-back MVP Awards. In 2016, Creedon was also named ESPNBoston Mr. Baseball for best player in the state throughout the season. ==Voting process== The press attending and covering the tournament vote on the Most Valuable Player during the game. The award is distributed by [[ESPN]]Boston.com<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://espn.go.com/blog/boston/high-school/post/_/id/32776/norths-sbordone-is-espn-bostons-super-8-mvp|title=North's Sbordone is ESPN Boston's Super 8 MVP|access-date=2016-07-08}}</ref> The Most Valuable Player is announced following the awarding of trophies to the runner-up and championship teams. If a second game of the championship series is necessary, the ballots taken during the second game are discarded, and a new round of balloting is conducted during the third and deciding game. == List == {| class="wikitable" |+Key ! scope="row" |Year |Links to the article about that corresponding Super Eight |- ! scope="row" style="background:#ffb;" |{{center|{{dagger}}}} |Member of the [[National Baseball Hall of Fame and Museum|Baseball Hall of Fame]] |- ! scope="row" style="background:#fbb;" |{{center|§}} |Indicates team did not win the tournament |} {| class="wikitable sortable plainrowheaders" style="text-align:center" |+Winners ! scope="col" |Year ! scope="col" |Name ! scope="col" |Position ! scope="col" |School |- |[[2014 MIAA Division IA Baseball Tournament|2014]] ! scope="row" style="text-align:center" |[[Dylan Sbordone]] |[[Pitcher]] |[[Newton North High School|Newton North]] |- |[[2015 MIAA Division IA Baseball Tournament|2015]] ! scope="row" style="text-align:center" |[[Scott Creedon]] |[[Pitcher]]/[[Shortstop]] |[[Braintree High School|Braintree]] |- |[[2016 MIAA Division IA Baseball Tournament|2016]] |[[Scott Creedon]] |[[Pitcher]]/[[Shortstop]] |[[Braintree High School|Braintree]] |}
